Produce Inventory Manager
A simple C++ console application that reads a list of purchased items from a text file and tracks quantities of produce using object-oriented programming.

Author:
	Alexandria D. Scott – SNHU – CS 210

Features:
  -	Reads items sold from text file (one item per line)
  -	Automatically groups identical items and counts occurrences
  -	Supports basic produce tracking
    o	Name & quantity
    o	Name & histogram
    o	Search by name
  -	Creates backup file of item names and frequencies

Project Structure
  Project_root/
    |--Project3.cpp
    |--Produce.h
    |--Produce.cpp
    |--Inventory.h
    |--Inventory.cpp
    |--Items_Shopped.txt
    |--frequencies.dat
 
Design Overview
  -	Produce class represents one type of item (name & count)
  -	Inventory class manages a collection of Produce instances
    o	Checks for duplicates
    o	Increments count when item already exist
    o	Prints names and counts of items
    o	Searches based on name and displays information
  -	Creates backup in new file
  -	User interaction takes place in main function
  
Limitations
  -	Linear search will be slow for very large lists
  -	No sorting output ability
  -	Minimal error handling
    o	Error handling for main menu is complete
    o	No error handling for capitalization errors in search function
  -	No ability to change data from menu

